thread.title: CSX quarterly profit dips, but EPS above Wall St consensus
thread.title_full: CSX quarterly profit dips, but EPS above Wall St consensus | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: CSX quarterly profit dips, but EPS above Wall St consensus
text:
CHICAGO Oct 13 No. 3 U.S. railroad CSX Corp on Tuesday reported a slightly lower quarterly net profit as revenues were driven down primarily by slumping coal volumes, but its earnings beat expectations thanks in part to cost-reduction initiatives.
The Jacksonville, Florida-based company reported third-quarter net income of $507 million or 52 cents per share, down from $509 million or 51 cents per share a year earlier.
Analysts had on average expected earnings per share of 50 cents.
(Reporting By Nick Carey ; Editing by Chris Reese )
